The memorandum is a delegation of authority from President Joseph R. Biden Jr. to the Secretary of State regarding the Foreign Assistance Act of 1961. The Secretary of State is granted the authority to direct the drawdown of up to $60 million in defense articles and services from the Department of Defense, as well as military education and training, to provide assistance to Ukraine. The Secretary of State is also responsible for making the necessary determinations required under the section mentioned to initiate the drawdown. The memorandum concludes by instructing the publication of this delegation in the Federal Register.